column5: Looks like a great weekend! Nice fish. Way to go!

Yep it was great to see you guys glad you could make it to the anual outting for one of crews Bday I will not say who is the old bugger or gal for this year but it seems the only way they know how to spend there Bday is on the water and that is great. Cant wait for the next one
Nice muskies Joey!  Congrats.  007
Nice fish for sure.
Awesome outing....
Nice fish Joey!!!!!!  Maybe someday it'll be my turn. I'd still be vibrating too. Man is that big'n clean looking .... like green chrome baby. You gotta love it!
Congrats!  Looks like you guys had a blast out there.  The fish are always the added icing on the cake.
Well done Joey! Let me know when you guys want to do it again and I'll drag Chris out of the house. He needs a muskie soon or we'll have to remove it from his name and just call him studd!
Looks like a great tome, congrats on the fish Joey!
great report, im glad to see you caught some real nice skis!

Joey,...Nice outing INDEED! How could it not have been with the oldschool OFC'rs you two were out with. What were your party....2-3 shy of the original 12  ???? Your looking very healthy Joey...we can see it in your eyes. Pauls turn will be next with the monster of all girls from the deep. Nice fish, great company and it looks like great weather....... Thanks for this report.  edit:( with the slow down load we have , only managed 3 pics but they were enough for us to enjoy)
Great pictures and report! LOL a little photoshop? all those OFC`ers  and no beer?
Wow Joey!!! Amazing report...and congrats on those muskies!!  Looking forward to Quinte and seeing you and Paul again.

Now that right there is funny  Thanks for the morning laugh.  Thanks everyone, I'm still beaming today.  Gonna head off to work and try not to look like a moron with this stupid grin that seems to be permanently fixed on my face  Joey
CONGRATS JOEY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  You nust have been in someone elses boat!!!!!!!
Great fish Joey, CONGRATS!!!

Whew w w w  w . . . .   ya sure know how to hurt a guy on dial-up, eh? Just had to get a boo at all the shots though . . .  looked like a great time was had by all! I just gotta get a shot at a musky some day . . . .    that hawg you're holding like a baby looks big enough to eat my biggest trout for breakfast!
Those St. Claire muskies are unique looking. Great late fall report!   rhg
Wow,  I didn't think you could be hotter out of the cooler, babe!   Is it me or does Mr.Eh look like Lews lovechild??
....Now that's a great way to spend a weekend. Super report Joey and nice, very nice fish. Well done.
Thanks for the report Joey.  Couple nice skis there.  You go girl. lol.

Spent the weekend with a small group of OFC'rs and had just a fabulous time.  The weather on the first day was a bit windy but after a great breakfast lakeside we braved it.    But by the afternoon, as you can see, the wind calmed down and the sun came out.    Don and Ruth I really enjoyed your company this weekend    Mr. Eh it was nice meeting you and Pete and Lew, a pleasure as always.    Now to the fish porn.  I hooked this beauty Saturday afternoon and I'm still vibrating from the excitement    The sun went down and then we all headed to dinner.  I can still hear that waitress humming     Sandy, you look fabulous as usual and Adam, thanks again, it really was a super time      Pete, you said I could post this, remember      More fish porn on Sunday.    And Wayne, the net is NOT jinxed    This morning was overcast, but warmer, and we tried for a few more hours so Paul wouldn't go home skunked, but ran out of time and had to check out.  We did notice another boat poaching (as Lew mentioned in this thread).  It was a black Lund and there were three guys and 7 lines.  I took a pic, but it turned out all fuzzy from the zoom  Thanks again everyone, I will remember this trip for a long time.  Joey & Paul
Fantastic report Joey! I was really looking forward to this one. Great pics also  and...you look just MAHVELOUS DAHLINK!
WTG Joey!  Nice looking skis!  Congrats on getting to slime the new net!   Maybe next time Paul
Sweet! Maybe Paul's hat scared them off his line! LOL Great pics and fish Joey! Congrats! HH
Congrat's Joey, beautiful fish!, sounds like a perfect trip.
Awesome pics!!!
get report looks like a great time
Well done Joey!  Couldn't ask for better company and fish to boot  Thanks for sharing!
I told you there was nothing wrong with that net ! LOL  And Lew looks like he's heard this story before....    Sounds like everyone had a great time and you got the bonus' of the weekend dear!

Always nice spending time with you & Paul, Joey, and the fish pic turned out excellent, and congrats again on that one, it's a real beauty......guess that'll be enlarged & hung on the wall ??  Good to hear you enjoyed yourself, but with the crew we had down there this weekend, it was hard not to have a great time.  Here's the picture I took of you & Paul on the dock last night.  See you guys next year.......same time, same place     And Wayne, I've heard em all, bud
Nice fish Im jealous.

Great report joey !!!! sounds like a good time had by all.  ...too bad you & paul didnt get into some of those big giants in lake st.clair !!! but fishing with freinds and having fun is all worth it anytime..great pics too.  ..cheers
Very nice, Joanne.  Tell us all the details on the weekend, 'k?
Great report and pic's Joey...  congrats... sure looks like a great time was had by all...
Great stuff Joey, glad everyone had a great time, congrats on some nice fish too  Maureen
Congrats Joey those are two beautiful fish !
great report and congrats on the fish
Great report Joey and thanks for the great weekend!! It was a blast!
Great Stuff Joey.   I seem to miss out on a lot of the fun times living down here.   I
WTG Joey, super fish.  Any day out on the water is a great day.  Now can you do a repeat in the BOQ
Congrats on the beautiful catch Joey.  Great report, thanks for sharing.
Nice going Joey.  You put together a great group of all-stars for your outing.  I may have detected a secret in one of the photos.  Time will tell.  Thanks for the report.
WOW atta girl WTG, fantastic report...
Nice Muskie Joey!
WTG Girl nice lookin fish.Oh and Paul nice job putting Joey on fish and an even better job with the net
